   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4, \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\"kernelspec\": {\"display_name\": \"Python 3\", \"language\": \"python\", \"name\": \"python3\"}, \"language_info\": {\"name\": \"python\", \"version\": \"3.11.0\"}},\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"# Agentic Research Assistant\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**NLP Project 94 of 100 · Advanced and Research-Style NLP**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This notebook builds an **agentic research assistant** that follows a multi-step pipeline: **search → retrieve → summarize → self-check**. The agent decomposes research questions, retrieves evidence from a document corpus using dense embeddings, generates answers, and then verifies whether its answers are grounded in the retrieved evidence.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Models:** Sentence-Transformers (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) for retrieval, TF-IDF baseline, extractive summarization\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Metrics:** Retrieval recall@k, groundedness score, answer quality\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Build a multi-step agentic NLP pipeline with explicit tool-use steps\\n\", \"2. Implement dense retrieval using sentence-transformers\\n\", \"3. Add a self-checking mechanism that verifies answer groundedness\\n\", \"4. Compare single-step vs. multi-step agent architectures\\n\", \"5. Understand failure modes in agentic NLP systems\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Given a research question, the agent must:\\n\", \"1. **Search** — identify relevant documents from a knowledge base\\n\", \"2. **Retrieve** — rank and select the most relevant passages\\n\", \"3. **Summarize** — synthesize retrieved passages into a coherent answer\\n\", \"4. **Self-check** — verify the answer is supported by the retrieved evidence\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This mirrors how modern RAG agents operate in production.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Agentic architectures are the foundation of modern AI assistants\\n\", \"- Self-checking reduces hallucination by catching unsupported claims\\n\", \"- Multi-step reasoning produces more accurate, grounded answers\\n\", \"- Understanding agent failure modes is critical for production deployment\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|----------|-------|\\n\", \"| Source | Synthetic knowledge base (ML/AI research topics) |\\n\", \"| KB Size | 20 research passages |\\n\", \"| Test Queries | 8 research questions |\\n\", \"| Language | English |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"All knowledge base passages and test queries are synthetically generated within this notebook.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Environment Setup\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Required packages: `sentence-transformers`, `scikit-learn`, `numpy`, `pandas`, `matplotlib`\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Imports\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"import json, os, warnings, textwrap\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib\\n\", \"matplotlib.use(\\\"Agg\\\")\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity as sklearn_cosine\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"SAVE_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(\\\"__file__\\\"))\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"np.random.seed(SEED)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Imports loaded.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Configuration / Constants\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"TOP_K = 3\\n\", \"GROUNDING_THRESHOLD = 0.4\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top-K: {TOP_K}, Grounding threshold: {GROUNDING_THRESHOLD}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We define a knowledge base of ML/AI research passages and test questions.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"KB = [\\n\", \"    \\\"BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) was introduced by Google in 2018. It uses masked language modeling and next sentence prediction for pre-training. BERT achieved state-of-the-art results on 11 NLP benchmarks.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) uses autoregressive language modeling. GPT-3 has 175 billion parameters and demonstrated strong few-shot learning capabilities without fine-tuning.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) combines a retriever component with a generator. The retriever finds relevant documents, and the generator produces answers conditioned on retrieved context. RAG reduces hallucination by grounding outputs in evidence.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Transformers use self-attention mechanisms to process input sequences in parallel. The attention mechanism computes query-key-value interactions, allowing the model to attend to relevant parts of the input regardless of distance.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Fine-tuning adapts a pre-trained model to a specific downstream task by training on task-specific data. LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) is a parameter-efficient fine-tuning method that freezes base weights and trains low-rank adapter matrices.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"RLHF (Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback) aligns language models with human preferences. A reward model is trained on human preference data, then used to optimize the language model via PPO or DPO.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Knowledge distillation trains a smaller student model to mimic a larger teacher model. The student learns from soft probability distributions produced by the teacher, capturing more nuanced knowledge than hard labels alone.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Prompt engineering involves crafting input prompts to elicit desired behavior from language models. Techniques include zero-shot, few-shot, chain-of-thought, and tree-of-thought prompting.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Vector databases store embeddings for efficient similarity search. FAISS, Pinecone, Weaviate, and Chroma are popular choices. They enable retrieval of semantically similar documents in milliseconds.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Sentence-transformers produce fixed-size embeddings for sentences and paragraphs. Models like all-MiniLM-L6-v2 and BGE-M3 encode text into dense vectors suitable for semantic search and clustering.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Evaluation of language models includes perplexity, BLEU, ROUGE, and human evaluation. For RAG systems, retrieval recall, answer faithfulness, and groundedness are critical metrics.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Attention mechanisms were first proposed in neural machine translation by Bahdanau et al. (2014). The transformer architecture by Vaswani et al. (2017) replaced recurrence entirely with self-attention.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Tokenization converts text into numerical tokens. Subword tokenization methods like BPE (Byte-Pair Encoding), WordPiece, and SentencePiece handle unknown words by breaking them into subword units.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Transfer learning in NLP leverages knowledge from pre-trained models trained on large corpora. Models like BERT, GPT, and T5 transfer linguistic knowledge to downstream tasks with minimal task-specific training.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Chain-of-thought (CoT) prompting encourages language models to produce intermediate reasoning steps before arriving at a final answer. This technique significantly improves performance on complex reasoning tasks.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Hallucination in language models refers to generating text that is fluent but factually incorrect or unsupported by the input context. Mitigation strategies include RAG, constrained decoding, and self-consistency checks.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"DSPy is a framework for optimizing modular LLM programs. It treats prompts as learnable parameters and uses teleprompters (optimizers) to find effective prompt configurations automatically.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Mixture of Experts (MoE) architectures use multiple specialized sub-networks. A gating mechanism routes each input to the most relevant experts, allowing scaling model capacity without proportional compute increase.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Constitutional AI (CAI) trains models to be helpful, harmless, and honest using a set of constitutional principles. The model critiques and revises its own outputs based on these principles.\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"Sparse attention mechanisms reduce the quadratic complexity of standard attention. Methods like Longformer, BigBird, and Flash Attention enable processing of longer sequences more efficiently.\\\",\\n\", \"]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"TEST_QUERIES = [\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"How does RAG reduce hallucination?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [2, 15]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"What is the difference between BERT and GPT?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [0, 1]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"How does knowledge distillation work?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [6]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"What are the main evaluation metrics for RAG systems?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [10, 2]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"Explain chain-of-thought prompting.\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [14, 7]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"What is LoRA and how does it relate to fine-tuning?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [4]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"How do vector databases enable semantic search?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [8, 9]},\\n\", \"    {\\\"q\\\": \\\"What is DSPy used for?\\\", \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\": [16]},\\n\", \"]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"KB: {len(KB)} passages, Test queries: {len(TEST_QUERIES)}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Data Validation Checks\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"assert len(KB) >= 15\\n\", \"for doc in KB:\\n\", \"    assert len(doc.split()) > 15\\n\", \"for q in TEST_QUERIES:\\n\", \"    assert \\\"q\\\" in q and \\\"expected_doc_idx\\\" in q\\n\", \"print(\\\"Validation passed.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Exploratory Data Analysis\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"doc_lens = [len(d.split()) for d in KB]\\n\", \"print(f\\\"KB passage lengths: mean={np.mean(doc_lens):.0f}, min={min(doc_lens)}, max={max(doc_lens)}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\\n\", \"ax.hist(doc_lens, bins=10, color=\\\"steelblue\\\", edgecolor=\\\"white\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Passage Length (words)\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Count\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"KB Passage Length Distribution\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"eda_distributions.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The target is a grounded answer for each research question. Quality is measured by retrieval recall, answer correctness, and groundedness.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"No train/test split — this is a pre-trained retrieval + generation pipeline evaluated on 8 test queries.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Encode KB passages into dense embeddings using sentence-transformers. Build TF-IDF index as baseline.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer\\n\", \"\\n\", \"st_model = SentenceTransformer(\\\"all-MiniLM-L6-v2\\\")\\n\", \"kb_embeddings = st_model.encode(KB, normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Dense embeddings: {kb_embeddings.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words=\\\"english\\\", ngram_range=(1, 2))\\n\", \"tfidf_matrix = tfidf.fit_transform(KB)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"TF-IDF matrix: {tfidf_matrix.shape}\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Dense embeddings capture semantic meaning; TF-IDF captures lexical overlap.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**TF-IDF retrieval + first-passage answer.**\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def tfidf_retrieve(query, top_k=TOP_K):\\n\", \"    q_vec = tfidf.transform([query])\\n\", \"    sims = sklearn_cosine(q_vec, tfidf_matrix).flatten()\\n\", \"    top_idx = sims.argsort()[-top_k:][::-1]\\n\", \"    return [(int(i), float(sims[i])) for i in top_idx]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"=== TF-IDF Baseline ===\\\")\\n\", \"for tq in TEST_QUERIES[:3]:\\n\", \"    results = tfidf_retrieve(tq[\\\"q\\\"])\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Q: {tq['q']}\\\")\\n\", \"    for idx, score in results:\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"  [{idx}] score={score:.3f} | {KB[idx][:60]}...\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for agentic retrieval-generation tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Not applicable** for agentic retrieval-generation tasks.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Agentic Pipeline: Search → Retrieve → Summarize → Self-Check\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The core agent implements four steps:\\n\", \"1. **Search**: Encode query and compute similarity against KB\\n\", \"2. **Retrieve**: Select top-K passages\\n\", \"3. **Summarize**: Combine retrieved passages into a coherent answer\\n\", \"4. **Self-check**: Verify answer groundedness via embedding similarity\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def dense_retrieve(query, top_k=TOP_K):\\n\", \"    q_emb = st_model.encode([query], normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"    sims = (q_emb @ kb_embeddings.T).flatten()\\n\", \"    top_idx = sims.argsort()[-top_k:][::-1]\\n\", \"    return [(int(i), float(sims[i])) for i in top_idx]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"def extractive_summarize(passages):\\n\", \"    all_sents = []\\n\", \"    for p in passages:\\n\", \"        sents = [s.strip() + \\\".\\\" for s in p.split(\\\".\\\") if len(s.strip()) > 20]\\n\", \"        all_sents.extend(sents)\\n\", \"    if len(all_sents) <= 3:\\n\", \"        return \\\" \\\".join(all_sents) if all_sents else passages[0]\\n\", \"    sent_tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(stop_words=\\\"english\\\").fit_transform(all_sents)\\n\", \"    scores = sent_tfidf.sum(axis=1).A1\\n\", \"    top_sent_idx = sorted(scores.argsort()[-3:][::-1])\\n\", \"    return \\\" \\\".join([all_sents[i] for i in top_sent_idx])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"def self_check(answer, passages):\\n\", \"    answer_emb = st_model.encode([answer], normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"    passage_embs = st_model.encode(passages, normalize_embeddings=True)\\n\", \"    sims = (answer_emb @ passage_embs.T).flatten()\\n\", \"    max_sim = float(sims.max())\\n\", \"    return {\\\"grounded\\\": max_sim >= GROUNDING_THRESHOLD, \\\"max_support\\\": round(max_sim, 4), \\\"avg_support\\\": round(float(sims.mean()), 4)}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"def agent_answer(question):\\n\", \"    results = dense_retrieve(question)\\n\", \"    passages = [KB[idx] for idx, _ in results]\\n\", \"    answer = extractive_summarize(passages)\\n\", \"    check = self_check(answer, passages)\\n\", \"    return {\\\"question\\\": question, \\\"answer\\\": answer, \\\"retrieved_idx\\\": [i for i,_ in results],\\n\", \"            \\\"retrieval_scores\\\": [s for _,s in results], **check}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"Agent pipeline defined.\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(\\\"=== Agent Answers ===\\\")\\n\", \"agent_results = []\\n\", \"for tq in TEST_QUERIES:\\n\", \"    result = agent_answer(tq[\\\"q\\\"])\\n\", \"    result[\\\"expected_idx\\\"] = tq[\\\"expected_doc_idx\\\"]\\n\", \"    agent_results.append(result)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\nQ: {result['question']}\\\")\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"A: {textwrap.fill(result['answer'][:200], width=100)}\\\")\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  Retrieved: {result['retrieved_idx']} | Expected: {result['expected_idx']}\\\")\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"  Grounded: {result['grounded']} (support: {result['max_support']:.3f})\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We compare TF-IDF vs Dense retrieval within the agent pipeline.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"def recall_at_k(retrieved, expected):\\n\", \"    return len(set(retrieved) & set(expected)) / len(expected)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dense_recalls, tfidf_recalls = [], []\\n\", \"for tq in TEST_QUERIES:\\n\", \"    d_idx = [i for i,_ in dense_retrieve(tq[\\\"q\\\"])]\\n\", \"    t_idx = [i for i,_ in tfidf_retrieve(tq[\\\"q\\\"])]\\n\", \"    dense_recalls.append(recall_at_k(d_idx, tq[\\\"expected_doc_idx\\\"]))\\n\", \"    tfidf_recalls.append(recall_at_k(t_idx, tq[\\\"expected_doc_idx\\\"]))\\n\", \"\\n\", \"grounding_scores = [r[\\\"max_support\\\"] for r in agent_results]\\n\", \"grounded_pct = sum(1 for r in agent_results if r[\\\"grounded\\\"]) / len(agent_results) * 100\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Recall@3 — TF-IDF: {np.mean(tfidf_recalls):.3f}, Dense: {np.mean(dense_recalls):.3f}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Grounded: {grounded_pct:.0f}%, Avg support: {np.mean(grounding_scores):.3f}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\", \"axes[0].bar([\\\"TF-IDF\\\", \\\"Dense\\\"], [np.mean(tfidf_recalls), np.mean(dense_recalls)], color=[\\\"coral\\\", \\\"steelblue\\\"])\\n\", \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Recall@3\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"Retrieval Quality\\\")\\n\", \"axes[0].set_ylim(0, 1)\\n\", \"axes[1].bar(range(len(grounding_scores)), grounding_scores, color=[\\\"green\\\" if r[\\\"grounded\\\"] else \\\"red\\\" for r in agent_results])\\n\", \"axes[1].axhline(GROUNDING_THRESHOLD, color=\\\"black\\\", linestyle=\\\"--\\\", label=f\\\"Threshold={GROUNDING_THRESHOLD}\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Query Index\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_ylabel(\\\"Support Score\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"Answer Groundedness\\\")\\n\", \"axes[1].legend()\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.savefig(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"evaluation.png\\\"), dpi=150, bbox_inches=\\\"tight\\\")\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Error Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Cases where retrieval misses expected documents or answers are not grounded indicate agent failure modes.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"print(\\\"=== Error Analysis ===\\\")\\n\", \"for r in agent_results:\\n\", \"    missed = set(r[\\\"expected_idx\\\"]) - set(r[\\\"retrieved_idx\\\"])\\n\", \"    if missed or not r[\\\"grounded\\\"]:\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"Q: {r['question'][:60]}\\\")\\n\", \"        if missed: print(f\\\"  MISSED: {list(missed)}\\\")\\n\", \"        if not r[\\\"grounded\\\"]: print(f\\\"  NOT GROUNDED (support={r['max_support']:.3f})\\\")\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Dense retrieval outperforms TF-IDF for semantic matching\\n\", \"2. Self-checking catches weak answers with low support scores\\n\", \"3. Each agent step is independently testable and replaceable\\n\", \"4. Production agents need iterative retrieval and LLM generation\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Small KB (20 passages) — far below production scale\\n\", \"2. Extractive only — no abstractive generation\\n\", \"3. No iterative retrieval on low-confidence answers\\n\", \"4. Synthetic queries — real research questions are more complex\\n\", \"5. No tool use (web search, calculators)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Add Qwen3-Instruct for abstractive answer generation\\n\", \"2. Iterative retrieval — re-query if support score is low\\n\", \"3. Web search tool for questions not in KB\\n\", \"4. Query decomposition for complex multi-hop questions\\n\", \"5. Convert to Haystack agent architecture\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Vector database (FAISS/Chroma) for scale\\n\", \"- Qwen3-Instruct for abstractive synthesis\\n\", \"- Trace every agent step for debugging\\n\", \"- Add guardrails on generated answers\\n\", \"- Collect user feedback to improve retrieval\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Mistake | Fix |\\n\", \"|---------|-----|\\n\", \"| No self-check | Always verify against evidence |\\n\", \"| Single retrieval step | Add iterative/multi-hop retrieval |\\n\", \"| No logging | Trace every step |\\n\", \"| Trusting LLM output | Ground every claim in evidence |\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Add iterative retrieval when groundedness is low\\n\", \"2. Combine TF-IDF and dense scores with weighted fusion\\n\", \"3. Build multi-hop queries requiring 2+ passages\\n\", \"4. Include passage citations in generated answers\\n\", \"5. Build automated agent evaluation metrics\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"markdown\", \"metadata\": {}, \"source\": [\"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| # | Takeaway |\\n\", \"|---|----------|\\n\", \"| 1 | Agentic pipelines (search → retrieve → summarize → check) provide transparent, grounded answers |\\n\", \"| 2 | Dense retrieval outperforms TF-IDF for semantic research questions |\\n\", \"| 3 | Self-checking via embedding similarity catches low-quality answers |\\n\", \"| 4 | Production agents need iterative retrieval, LLM generation, and tracing |\\n\", \"| 5 | Each agent step should be independently testable and replaceable |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"---\\n\", \"*NLP Project 94 of 100 · Advanced and Research-Style NLP*\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\": \"code\", \"execution_count\": null, \"metadata\": {}, \"outputs\": [], \"source\": [\"metrics = {\\n\", \"    \\\"project\\\": \\\"Agentic Research Assistant\\\",\\n\", \"    \\\"kb_size\\\": len(KB),\\n\", \"    \\\"test_queries\\\": len(TEST_QUERIES),\\n\", \"    \\\"dense_recall_at_3\\\": round(float(np.mean(dense_recalls)), 4),\\n\", \"    \\\"tfidf_recall_at_3\\\": round(float(np.mean(tfidf_recalls)), 4),\\n\", \"    \\\"grounded_pct\\\": round(grounded_pct, 1),\\n\", \"    \\\"avg_support_score\\\": round(float(np.mean(grounding_scores)), 4),\\n\", \"}\\n\", \"with open(os.path.join(SAVE_DIR, \\\"metrics.json\\\"), \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n\", \"    json.dump(metrics, f, indent=2)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Saved: metrics.json\\\")\\n\", \"print(json.dumps(metrics, indent=2))\"]}\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
   ],
